    <h1>Adrift&#x2019;s Re&#xAD;vamped Week&#xAD;end Brunch Menu</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20200828/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-08-28"><time>2020-08-28</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE HAPPENINGS</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Adrift by David My­ers ’ re­vamped week­end brunch menu of­fers more than 15 brunch op­tions. In ad­di­tion to sta­ples such as New Eng­land lob­ster frit­tata and king crab omelette, din­ers can en­joy orig­i­nal creations such as the goat’s curd waf­fle with smoked maple syrup and bacon ice cream. There is also the Have It Chef’s Way brunch ($45++ for two hours), in which the chefs cu­rate the items. Adrift of­fers a free-flow bev­er­age pack­age – all din­ers at the ta­ble must have a drink, with one glass served at a time.</p>
    <p>WHERE: Adrift by David My­ers, Ma­rina Bay Sands, Lobby Tower 2 Ho­tel, 10 Bayfront Ave MRT: Bayfront</p>
    <p>WHEN: Sat & Sun, 11.30am - 3pm TEL: 6688-5657 INFO: str.sg/J7PJ</p>


